<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,265,544]" pageId="7" pageNumber="200">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,430,373,400]" pageId="7" pageNumber="200">Taxonomic notes:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boissier" authorityYear="1862" box="[429,657,374,400]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="200" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="foliolosa">
<emphasis box="[429,657,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="200">Euphorbia foliolosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus (1759:" authorityYear="1048" box="[871,1040,374,400]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="200" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hyssopifolia">
<emphasis box="[871,1040,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="200">E. hyssopifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boissier" authorityYear="1862" baseAuthorityName="Klotzsch &amp; Garcke" box="[1099,1239,374,400]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="200" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bahiensis">
<emphasis box="[1099,1239,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="200">E. bahiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but may be easily identified among them by its longer (&gt; 
<quantity box="[585,672,410,437]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="7" pageNumber="200" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
in 
<emphasis box="[710,879,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="200">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boissier" authorityYear="1862" box="[710,840,410,436]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="200" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="foliolosa">E. foliolosa</taxonomicName>
vs.
</emphasis>
up to 
<quantity box="[954,1041,410,437]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="7" pageNumber="200" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus (1759:" authorityYear="1048" box="[1079,1246,410,436]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="200" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hyssopifolia">
<emphasis box="[1079,1246,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="200">E. hyssopifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boissier" authorityYear="1862" baseAuthorityName="Klotzsch &amp; Garcke" box="[1304,1442,410,436]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="200" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bahiensis">
<emphasis box="[1304,1442,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="200">E. bahiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and entire (
<emphasis box="[264,294,447,472]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="200">vs.</emphasis>
bifid in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus (1759:" authorityYear="1048" box="[391,557,446,472]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="200" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hyssopifolia">
<emphasis box="[391,557,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="200">E. hyssopifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boissier" authorityYear="1862" baseAuthorityName="Klotzsch &amp; Garcke" box="[612,750,446,472]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="200" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bahiensis">
<emphasis box="[612,750,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="200">E. bahiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) styles, and venation pattern (cladodromous in 
<emphasis box="[1284,1451,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="200">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boissier" authorityYear="1862" box="[1284,1414,446,472]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="200" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="foliolosa">E. foliolosa</taxonomicName>
vs.
</emphasis>
actinodromous in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus (1759:" authorityYear="1048" box="[342,510,482,508]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="200" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hyssopifolia">
<emphasis box="[342,510,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="200">E. hyssopifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boissier" authorityYear="1862" baseAuthorityName="Klotzsch &amp; Garcke" box="[568,707,482,508]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="200" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bahiensis">
<emphasis box="[568,707,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="200">E. bahiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). One notable characteristic of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boissier" authorityYear="1862" box="[1069,1200,482,508]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="200" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="foliolosa">
<emphasis box="[1069,1200,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="200">E. foliolosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, besides its very long styles, is the blackish apex of the teeth of the leaf margin.
</paragraph>
